FREE(1)                          User Commands                         FREE(1)

NAME
       free - display amount of free and used memory in the system

SYNOPSIS
       free [options]

DESCRIPTION
       free displays the total amount of free and used physical and swap
       memory in the system, as well as the buffers and caches used by
       the kernel.  The information is gathered from the sysinfo syscall.

OPTIONS
       -b, --bytes
              show output in bytes

       --kilo show output in kilobytes (1000-based)

       --mega show output in megabytes (1000-based)

       --giga show output in gigabytes (1000-based)

       --tera show output in terabytes (1000-based)

       --peta show output in petabytes (1000-based)

       -k, --kibi
              show output in kibibytes (default)

       -m, --mebi
              show output in mebibytes

       -g, --gibi
              show output in gibibytes

       --tebi show output in tebibytes

       --pebi show output in pebibytes

       -h, --human
              show human-readable output (powers of 1024)

       --si   use powers of 1000 instead of 1024

       -l, --lohi
              show detailed low and high memory statistics

       -L, --line
              show output on a single line

       -t, --total
              show total for RAM + swap

       -v, --committed
              show committed memory and commit limit

       -s, --seconds N
              repeat printing every N seconds

       -c, --count N
              repeat printing N times, then exit

       -w, --wide
              wide output (separate buffers and cache columns)

       --help display this help and exit

       -V, --version
              output version information and exit

AUTHORS
       LikeOS-64 project.

SEE ALSO
       top(1), ps(1), uptime(1)

